learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T20:40:45.847Z",maintainer-agent,"The trivial-docstring quality gate must subtract the symbol's own identifier tokens AND a tiny filler-word set from the prose, then flag only when zero meaningful words remain. Calibrated against all existing docstrings first (0 false positives) before enabling; enabling it repo-wide without that calibration would have failed the gate on legitimate terse docs."
  "2026-07-10T23:16:47.785Z",codex-gpt5,Repo-wide documentation changes can expose latent jscpd clones by shifting token windows; preserve the zero threshold by extracting shared behavioral primitives rather than excluding documented files or weakening detection.
